## Conversation
This stack is round 2 of the in-memory fake trace server. Round 1 (PRs
#7145-#7152 v3) replicated the SQLite trace server. The user then said:
'It seems like a lot of this stack tries to replicate the sqlite trace
server, when in reality it should probably replicate the clickhouse trace
server. Please update the stack accordingly.' Everything here is the
ClickHouse re-target: the fake now replicates ClickHouse (the production
backend) at the interface level, client_is_sqlite(client) is False for the
fake, and a new client_is_clickhouse(client) predicate gates tests that
assert ClickHouse *internals* (SQL, table routing/residence, batching,
bucket file storage, raw server._query access).

