## This commit (stage 4/10: feedback/costs + ORM evaluation)
Feedback and costs evaluate queries through an ORM-equivalent layer
mirroring what CH runs these tables through: _orm_field_value applies
JSON_VALUE-with-complex semantics plus a default 'string' cast,
mapContains existence, _OrmDatetimeLiteral normalizes datetime literals,
$contains with a numeric needle raises
clickhouse_connect.driver.exceptions.DatabaseError('Illegal type Int64|
Float64 of argument of function position') exactly like the driver.
feedback_aggregate is the newest method: master commit 5e73a213b4 (PR
#7043) added the endpoint mid-stack-rebuild, so the fake mirrors
build_feedback_aggregate_query row-at-a-time: WHERE (project, created_at
in [after_ms, before_ms), feedback_type prefix-any, monitor/scorer
object-id match where the id is ref.split('/')[-1].split(':')[0] and a
trailing '*' opts into prefix, span_agent_names IN, span_types via
weave_ref's second-to-last path segment, tags hasAny, rating bounds
require mapContains '_rating_'), GROUP BY epoch-aligned
toStartOfInterval bucket (int(ts // s) * s) plus group_by dims
(scorer_id derived from runnable_ref), sumMap-style tag/rating tallies,
scored_count = rows with any tag or rating, ORDER BY bucket (bucketed)
or group dims, and — critical CH behavior — a query with NO grouping
keys returns exactly ONE global rollup row even over zero rows.

